<section class="company-intro">
	<div class="maincontainer">
		<div class="row g-0">
						<div class="col-md-4 intro-col">
				<div class="intro-inner">
					<img src="wp-content/uploads/2025/02/question.png" alt="image">
					<h4>Who We Are</h4>
					<p>Yuwalaya is a purely youth-led, non-profit, non-government organization working for and with adolescents & youths of Nepal in order to help them enjoy their life to their fullest potential. The organization was formed by the child club graduates to guide child club graduates and youths and rekindle their interest in new and emerging issues of the youths and work as a bridge between child club members and youths to minimize the disputes between child club graduates, youths, and I/NGOs. </p>
					<a href="about-us/">Read More</a>
				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="col-md-4 intro-col">
				<div class="intro-inner">
					<img src="wp-content/uploads/2025/02/charity.png" alt="image">
					<h4>Whome We Help</h4>
					<p>At Yuwalaya, we focus on supporting adolescents and youth across Nepal, especially those who are marginalized, underserved, or facing systemic barriers. We work with young people from diverse backgrounds—including girls and young women, LGBTQIA+ individuals, youth with disabilities, and those affected by poverty or social exclusion. By providing safe spaces, resources, and opportunities for growth, we empower them to speak up, lead, and drive change in their communities. Our programs are designed to be inclusive and youth-centered, ensuring that every young person has the tools and support they need to thrive.</p>
					<a href="about-us/">Read More</a>
				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="col-md-4 intro-col">
				<div class="intro-inner">
					<img src="wp-content/uploads/2025/02/globe.png" alt="image">
					<h4>What We Do</h4>
					<p>Yuwalaya is dedicated to empowering adolescents and youths, encouraging them to realize their fullest potential by participating in youth and adolescent movements, promoting leadership, and addressing emerging issues that impact their lives. Through its initiatives, Yuwalaya ensures that young voices are heard and included in decision-making processes across Nepal.</p>
					<a href="about-us/">Read More</a>
				</div>
			</div>
					</div>
	</div>
</section>
